news.title: DLF to launch 7.7 million sq ft of real estate projects in second half of FY22
news.para: DLF reported a net profit of Rs 378.12 crore for the quarter ended September, up 66% from Rs 227.75 crore a year earlier, buoyed by improved demand for residential real estate.

news.title: UK house price growth hits 15-year high: Halifax
news.para: House prices rose 3.4% in the three months to the end of November, the sharpest increase since late 2006, and are 8.2% higher than a year earlier, according to the monthly figures from the lender, part of Lloyds Banking Group.

news.title: Shriram Properties IPO subscribed 89% on day one
news.para: Shriram Properties on Tuesday said it has raised a little over Rs 268 crore from anchor investors ahead of its initial share-sale. The company decided to allocate 2,27,66,949 equity shares to anchor investors at Rs 118 apiece, valuing the transaction size to Rs 268.64 crore, according to a BSE circular.

news.title: Dubai regulator fines Emirates REIT manager over asset report
news.para: Equitativa made misleading statements on two occasions in 2018 regarding one of Emirates REIT's 11 assets, a school in Dubai Investment Park, the DFSA said.

news.title: Income tax department raids Sagar Group premises in Bhopal and Indore
news.para: Sagar Group is a giant real estate group, which also runs educational institutions and factories in Madhya Pradesh. I-T officials reached Sagar Group owner Sanjeev Agrawal's office in Bhopal's MP Nagar area and a heavy police force was deployed outside.

news.title: Cabinet approves continuation of PMAY-Gramin till March 2024
news.para: The total financial implication for construction of the remaining 155.75 lakh houses is Rs. 2,17,257 crore or achieving cumulative targets of 2.95 crore houses in rural areas under the PMAY-Gramin.

news.title: Gujarat HC tells lawyers to inspect tallest building in Gandhinagar
news.para: ​Petitioner’s counsel Hardik Pandit submitted that the civic body did not take action against the developer J K Infrastructure because of involvement of ex-mayor Ritaben Patel.

news.title: Runwal Group appoints Sangeeta Prasad as Group CEO
news.para: Prasad has previously worked in Tata Steel in multiple business roles and Mahindra Group where her last role was MD & CEO of Mahindra Lifespace Developers.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body officials to get property tax collection targets
news.para: BBMP chief commissioner Gaurav Gupta instructed his revenue officials and assistant revenue officials to ensure that citizens paid their property taxes and also asked them to issue notices to those who have defaulted and collect it immediately.

news.title: Tenantcube raises $250,000 in pre-seed round funding
news.para: The funds will be used for further expansion of the sales and service coordination team, to meet current and future demand.

news.title: Compass to hire around 100 employees in Hyderabad
news.para: The company currently has a headcount of 201 in India and will be hiring an additional 199 people this financial year across these three centres in the area of AI, ML and mobile, among others, said Compass chief technology officer (CTO) Joseph Sirosh

news.title: RBI keeps repo rate unchanged at 4%
news.para: The reverse repo rate -- the level at which it absorbs excess cash from lenders -- was kept unchanged at 3.35%. RBI kept the GDP growth projections unchanged at 9.5% for the current fiscal and retained the inflation forecast of 5.3 per cent for the full year.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to develop a Connaught Place-like commercial market
news.para: While the area has many residential and commercial units in its vicinity, it is also barely a kilometre from the Yamuna Expressway, and is expected to gain momentum with the commencement of the Jewar airport operations.

news.title: China Evergrande Group edges closer to default after missing debt deadline
news.para: Failure by Evergrande to make $82.5 million in interest payments due last month would trigger cross-default on its roughly $19 billion of international bonds and put the developer at risk of becoming China's biggest defaulter - a possibility looming over the world's second-largest economy for months.

news.title: Ludhiana: Developers asked to provide sale deeds for regularisation
news.para: Senior town planner Surinder Singh Bindra has written to assistant town planners about this. The sale deeds will help determine how many plots were sold in reality and weather the sale was conducted legally.
